            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. YouTube videos are automatically indexed by Google because YouTube is a Google property with full crawl access. Website-hosted videos require additional work: a video sitemap, VideoObject schema markup, and a crawlable video player. Without these signals, Google may index the page but not the video itself, which means missing out on video rich results.</p></div></div>
